===Noun phrase===
'''shilling sign''' (''plural'' '''shilling signs''')

#The symbol '/' used in the [[United Kingdom]] before [[decimalisation]] to separate [[shilling]]s from [[pence]] when writing out sums of money.  (Examples: 7/6 = seven shillings and six pence; 7/- = seven shillings exactly.)

